The purpose of this Wikibook is to provide a resource for those studying Women's Studies (or Feminism) at Undergraduate level. This book will include noteworthy feminist philosophies, branches of feminist philosophy, and noteworthy prominent feminists (focusing on their work as feminists). Feel free to contribute to this book to improve its teaching potential!
=== Status === As of October 2005, this book is still heavily under development. There are also many articles to be added. That said, given the influence of feminism on both society and academia within the past decade, it is definitely a worthwhile subject matter for a Wikibook. What appears here is a starting point. - [[User:AmishThrasher|AmishThrasher]] 02:04, 27 October 2005 (UTC)
